This is according to Njombo Lekula, Managing Director of Pretoria Portland Cement Company, PPC RSA, the leading supplier of cement in South Africa, who says that sub-standard cement products are threatening the built environment industry and placing South African lives at risk.Â 

The usage of sub-standard cement has various implications that may negatively affect the sustainability of buildings and structures, thereby leading to increased repair or maintenance costs, injuries and fatalities due to structural failures or collapse.

